The information I am about to provide is something that every EQ player MUST know.  Some of you more experienced EQ'ers are going to know this from the start, and undoubtedly agree with me.  But lately I have been noticing a lot of people who just don't know this.
   All types of characters have their benefits...some are obvious...others are not so obvious.  Clerics heal, Warriors fight, but what do enchanters do?
   We are not your drug dealers...we are good for more than Crack (Clarity spells...for you noobs).
   If properly implemented, an enchanter can be the best weapon your group can ever have.  The enchanter has the power to make MOB's (Mobiles - aka the critters you go around killing) powerless for certain periods of time...among other things.
   Chanters have the job title of "crowd control."  You got your main tank (puller), he runs off and grabs a MOB to bring to your group to kill.  Sometimes the tank pulls more than one MOB.  If you have a chanter, this is a great thing.
   We have this wonderful spell called Mez (The Mesmirise series).  It makes the MOB stand there, staring off into lala land while you beat the hell out of his little friend.  After you kill his friend off, you can then turn around and kill him.  This means that everyone can fight the same guy at one time...reducing the amount of damage everyone takes, and speeding up the killing process.  Clerics love this...less mana wasted healing everyone who was soloing in a group.
   Mez can be broken.  If you cause a MOB to break Mez...you WILL piss off the chanter.  All you have to do is a single point of damage.  If the chanter says, I got so and so mezzed...leave that MOB alone until everyone is ready to move on to it.  So that should be fairly obvious to the tanks and melee fighters, right? Don't hit it.
   Now for you magic users...you are notorious for causing problems out of ignorance.  Do not think to yourself...well, I will just weaken the MOB standing around.  With a nuke...Mez is like root, right?  WRONG. Well, how about a DoT (damage over time) spell?  NOOOO!!!  So magic users, if you have a chanter in the group...ask in advance who they will be mezzing.  Cause your DoT spell will cause your chanter a headache.  Everytime that spell does damage the MOB will wake up.  You do any damage to that MOB, he will come running...at the chanter.
   Because Mez is high on the aggro list...meaning that MOB is going be pissed off at the chanter...and come straight for him/her.  This will cause your cleric a headache...because chanters have like NO hitpoints.  Watch their health bar drop as a MOB hits it...it is kinda frightening.  Chanters are NOT tanks...they are wimps that hit like a girl...so to speak.  (Which is funny...cause I am a girl)
   So, everyone please...remember your roles.  And try to understand everyone else's.  Working together is not only easier, but if you do it right you can get a lot of awesome XP in a short amount of time.

Farethee Well,
Lillianne 
